 Dreal Bayelsa Pikin, a student of the Niger Delta University, Wilberforce Island, took to Facebook to cry out after rats ate parts of his reading materials in preparation for his exams slated for Friday, December 3. “See What I woke up to see. Amassoma Rats. What have you done. Material for today’s Exams Has Been Eaten. They want me to fail. Wetin I go read now?” he wailed.   